-  - When `true`, the rule requires that `catch` clauses have a parameter. If a `throw` statement appears inside a `catch` clause without a parameter, it will be flagged.
-
-**Invalid examples**:
-
-```js
-try {
-  foo();
-} catch {
-  throw new Error("fail");
-}
-```
-
